<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="563" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="563">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="563">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Mènètriès">Menetries</normalizedToken>
(1832) describes 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Neri &amp; Toledano" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Neri &amp; Toledano" baseAuthorityYear="1832" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bembidion (Peryphus) dimidiatum" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dimidiatum" subGenus="Peryphus">Bembidion (Peryphus) dimidiatum</taxonomicName>
from the banks of 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“Potkoumà”">&quot;Potkouma&quot;</normalizedToken>
near 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“Pétigorsk”">&quot;Petigorsk&quot;</normalizedToken>
on &quot;quelques individus&quot;. After the description, 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. dimidiatum" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" rank="species" species="dimidiatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">B. dimidiatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was retained as strictly related to 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. oblongum" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" rank="species" species="oblongum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">B. oblongum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Dejean, 1831 or 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. ripicola" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" rank="species" species="ripicola">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">B. ripicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Dufour, 1820 (currently all species belonging to the subgenus 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bembidion (Euperyphus)" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Euperyphus">Bembidion Euperyphus</taxonomicName>
Jeannel, 1941). 
<bibRefCitation author="Netolitzky, F" journalOrPublisher="Wiener Entomologische Zeitung" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" refId="B41" refString="Netolitzky, F, 1914a. Die Bembidiini in Winklers Catalogus. Entomologische Blatter 10(1/2): 50-55." title="Die Bembidiini in Winklers Catalogus. Entomologische Blatter 10 (1 / 2): 50 - 55." year="1914 a">Netolitzky (1914a)</bibRefCitation>
synonymized 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. dimidiatum" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" rank="species" species="dimidiatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">B. dimidiatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. tricolor" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" rank="species" species="tricolor">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">B. tricolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fabricius, 1801) (= 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. varicolor" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" rank="species" species="varicolor">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">B. varicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fabricius, 1803); the synonymy derives from the fact that the author examined Caucasian specimens identified as 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. dimidiatum" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" rank="species" species="dimidiatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">B. dimidiatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
actually belonging to 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. (Bembidionetolitzkya) varicolor" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" rank="species" species="varicolor" subGenus="Bembidionetolitzkya">B. (Bembidionetolitzkya) varicolor</taxonomicName>
and was perhaps unaware that this last species also occurs in the Caucasus and shares the same particular pattern of color of the European 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bembidion varicolor" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="varicolor">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">Bembidion varicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. But later (1935) the author himself retained 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. dimidiatum" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" rank="species" species="dimidiatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">B. dimidiatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as closely related to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1831" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bembidion oblongum" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oblongum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">Bembidion oblongum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and in any case not similar to 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. conforme" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" rank="species" species="conforme">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">B. conforme</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Dejean, 1831 or 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. tricolor" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" rank="species" species="tricolor">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">B. tricolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(both belonging to subgenus 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bembidion (Bembidionetolitzkya)" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Bembidionetolitzkya">Bembidion Bembidionetolitzkya</taxonomicName>
Strand, 1929). 
<bibRefCitation author="Netolitzky, F" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the Royal Entomological Society of London - Series B: Taxonomy" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" refId="B45" refString="Netolitzky, F, 1943a. Bestimmungs-Tabellen europaeischer Kaefer (9. Stück). II. Fam. Carabidae. Subfam. Bembidiinae. 66. Gattung: Bembidion Latr. Bestimmungstabelle der Bembidion-Arten des palaearktischen Gebietes. (Mit Hinweisen auf holarktische, aethiopische und orientalische Arten). Koleopterologische Rundschau 28(4/6): 69/41-124/96." title="Bestimmungs-Tabellen europaeischer Kaefer (9. Stu ̈ ck). II. Fam. Carabidae. Subfam. Bembidiinae. 66. Gattung: Bembidion Latr. Bestimmungstabelle der Bembidion-Arten des palaearktischen Gebietes. (Mit Hinweisen auf holarktische, aethiopische und orientalische Arten). Koleopterologische Rundschau 28 (4 / 6): 69 / 41 - 124 / 96." year="1943 a">Netolitzky (1943a</bibRefCitation>
: 112/84, note 83) reported that 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. dimidiatum" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" rank="species" species="dimidiatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">B. dimidiatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to the &quot;Gruppe des 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. ripicola" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" rank="species" species="ripicola">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">B. ripicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
- 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1831" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bembidion oblongum" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oblongum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">Bembidion oblongum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot; and retained it as close to 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. testaceum subsp. parallelipenne" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" rank="subSpecies" species="testaceum" subSpecies="parallelipenne">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">B. testaceum parallelipenne</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Chaudoir, 1850; moreover, 
<bibRefCitation author="Netolitzky, F" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the Royal Entomological Society of London - Series B: Taxonomy" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" refId="B46" refString="Netolitzky, F, 1943b. Bestimmungs-Tabellen europaeischer Kaefer (9. Stueck). II. Fam. Carabidae, Subfam. Bembidiinae. 66. Gattung: Bembidion Latr. Bestimmungstabelle der Bembidion-Arten des palaearktischen Gebietes. (Mit Hinweisen auf holarktische, aethiopische und orientalische Arten). Koleopterologische Rundschau 29: 1/97-70/166." title="Bestimmungs-Tabellen europaeischer Kaefer (9. Stueck). II. Fam. Carabidae, Subfam. Bembidiinae. 66. Gattung: Bembidion Latr. Bestimmungstabelle der Bembidion-Arten des palaearktischen Gebietes. (Mit Hinweisen auf holarktische, aethiopische und orientalische Arten). Koleopterologische Rundschau 29: 1 / 97 - 70 / 166." year="1943 b">Netolitzky (1943b</bibRefCitation>
: 17/113, note 18) mentioned that, if they were synonyms, 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. dimidiatum" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" rank="species" species="dimidiatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">B. dimidiatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should have priority over 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. parallelipenne" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" rank="species" species="parallelipenne">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">B. parallelipenne</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; he did not formally state in any way this synonymy. Later, Kryzhanovskij et al. (1995) and 
<bibRefCitation author="Lorenz, W" journalOrPublisher="Brill, Leiden-Boston" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" refId="B25" refString="Lorenz, W, 1998. Systematic List of Extant Ground Beetles of the World. Tutzing, 503 pp." title="Systematic List of Extant Ground Beetles of the World. Tutzing, 503 pp." year="1998">Lorenz (1998)</bibRefCitation>
listed 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. dimidiatum" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" rank="species" species="dimidiatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">B. dimidiatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. parallelipenne" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" rank="species" species="parallelipenne">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">B. parallelipenne</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but expressed doubts. 
<bibRefCitation author="Marggi, W" journalOrPublisher="Apollo Books, Stenstrup" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" refId="B28" refString="Marggi, W, Huber, C, Mueller-Motzfeld, G, Hartmann, M, 2003. Carabidae: Bembidiini: Bembidiina: 242-273. In: Loebl I, Smetana A (Eds) Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera (Vol. 1). Archostemata - Myxophaga - Adephaga. Apollo Books, Stenstrup" title="Carabidae: Bembidiini: Bembidiina: 242 - 273. In: Loebl I, Smetana A (Eds) Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera (Vol. 1). Archostemata - Myxophaga - Adephaga." year="2003">Marggi et al. (2003</bibRefCitation>
: 271) completely changed direction, moving 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Neri &amp; Toledano" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Neri &amp; Toledano" baseAuthorityYear="1832" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bembidion dimidiatum" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dimidiatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">Bembidion dimidiatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to &quot;incertae sedis&quot;, explaining the decision as follows: &quot; 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chaudoir" authorityYear="1850" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bembidion (Peryphus) parallelipenne" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="parallelipenne" subGenus="Peryphus">Bembidion (Peryphus) parallelipenne</taxonomicName>
? syn. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Neri &amp; Toledano" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Neri &amp; Toledano" baseAuthorityYear="1832" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bembidion dimidiatum" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dimidiatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">Bembidion dimidiatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken originalValue="Ménétriés">Menetries</normalizedToken>
, 1832, resurrected as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Neri &amp; Toledano" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Neri &amp; Toledano" baseAuthorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bembidion" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">Bembidion</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(incertae sedis) 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Neri &amp; Toledano" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Neri &amp; Toledano" baseAuthorityYear="1832" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bembidion dimidiatum" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dimidiatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">Bembidion dimidiatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken originalValue="Ménétriés">Menetries</normalizedToken>
, 1832. It is not a member of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Motschoulsky" authorityYear="1864" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Actedium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Actedium" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">Actedium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as given in Lorenz, 1998&quot; (
<bibRefCitation author="Marggi, W" journalOrPublisher="Apollo Books, Stenstrup" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" refId="B28" refString="Marggi, W, Huber, C, Mueller-Motzfeld, G, Hartmann, M, 2003. Carabidae: Bembidiini: Bembidiina: 242-273. In: Loebl I, Smetana A (Eds) Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera (Vol. 1). Archostemata - Myxophaga - Adephaga. Apollo Books, Stenstrup" title="Carabidae: Bembidiini: Bembidiina: 242 - 273. In: Loebl I, Smetana A (Eds) Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera (Vol. 1). Archostemata - Myxophaga - Adephaga." year="2003">Marggi et al. 2003</bibRefCitation>
: 21).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="563">
The same settlement is confirmed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Lorenz, W" journalOrPublisher="Brill, Leiden-Boston" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" refId="B26" refString="Lorenz, W, 2005. Systematic List of Extant Ground Beetles of the World (2nd edn.). Tutzing, 530 pp." title="Systematic List of Extant Ground Beetles of the World (2 nd edn.). Tutzing, 530 pp." year="2005">Lorenz (2005)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Marggi, W" journalOrPublisher="Brill, Leiden" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" refId="B29" refString="Marggi, W, Toledano, L, Neri, P, 2017. Carabidae: Bembidiini: Bembidiina: 294-342. In: Loebl I, Loebl D (Eds) Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera (Vol. I). Archostemata - Myxophaga - Adephaga. Brill, Leiden" title="Carabidae: Bembidiini: Bembidiina: 294 - 342. In: Loebl I, Loebl D (Eds) Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera (Vol. I). Archostemata - Myxophaga - Adephaga." year="2017">Marggi et al. (2017)</bibRefCitation>
. Unfortunately, the sentence of 
<bibRefCitation author="Marggi, W" journalOrPublisher="Apollo Books, Stenstrup" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" refId="B28" refString="Marggi, W, Huber, C, Mueller-Motzfeld, G, Hartmann, M, 2003. Carabidae: Bembidiini: Bembidiina: 242-273. In: Loebl I, Smetana A (Eds) Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera (Vol. 1). Archostemata - Myxophaga - Adephaga. Apollo Books, Stenstrup" title="Carabidae: Bembidiini: Bembidiina: 242 - 273. In: Loebl I, Smetana A (Eds) Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera (Vol. 1). Archostemata - Myxophaga - Adephaga." year="2003">Marggi et al. (2003)</bibRefCitation>
above and in particular the reference to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Motschoulsky" authorityYear="1864" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Actedium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Actedium" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">Actedium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
probably caused the moving of 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. dimidiatum" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" rank="species" species="dimidiatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">B. dimidiatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to &quot;incertae sedis&quot;, and are unclear; we verified that in 
<bibRefCitation author="Lorenz, W" journalOrPublisher="Brill, Leiden-Boston" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" refId="B25" refString="Lorenz, W, 1998. Systematic List of Extant Ground Beetles of the World. Tutzing, 503 pp." title="Systematic List of Extant Ground Beetles of the World. Tutzing, 503 pp." year="1998">Lorenz (1998)</bibRefCitation>
neither 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. parallelipenne" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" rank="species" species="parallelipenne">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">B. parallelipenne</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, nor 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. dimidiatum" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" rank="species" species="dimidiatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">B. dimidiatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are reported as belonging to the subgenus 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bembidion (Actedium)" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Actedium">Bembidion Actedium</taxonomicName>
. From the literature we ascertained that 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. dimidiatum" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" rank="species" species="dimidiatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">B. dimidiatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
certainly belongs to the subgenus 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bembidion (Euperyphus)" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Euperyphus">Bembidion Euperyphus</taxonomicName>
(as currently intended, see above); there still remains uncertainty regarding its precise position, with three (
<taxonomicName authority="parallelipenne" genus="B." lsidName="B. parallelipenne subsp. parallelipenne" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" rank="subSpecies" species="parallelipenne" subSpecies="parallelipenne">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">B. parallelipenne parallelipenne</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. parallelipenne subsp. exisonum" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" rank="subSpecies" species="parallelipenne" subSpecies="exisonum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">B. parallelipenne exisonum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Lutshnik, 1938, 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. parallelipenne subsp. pseudoripicola" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" rank="subSpecies" species="parallelipenne" subSpecies="pseudoripicola">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">B. parallelipenne pseudoripicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Iablokoff-Khnzorian, 1963) taxa currently assigned to the same group. In our opinion it seems unlikely that all the three Caucasian forms could be valid, and it would be necessary to verify them; in any case we suppose that the subspecies more similar to 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. dimidiatum" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" rank="species" species="dimidiatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">B. dimidiatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, mainly due to the elytral coloration, could be 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. pseudoripicola" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" rank="species" species="pseudoripicola">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">B. pseudoripicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; in case of possible synonymies the problem of priority already reported by 
<bibRefCitation author="Netolitzky, F" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the Royal Entomological Society of London - Series B: Taxonomy" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" refId="B46" refString="Netolitzky, F, 1943b. Bestimmungs-Tabellen europaeischer Kaefer (9. Stueck). II. Fam. Carabidae, Subfam. Bembidiinae. 66. Gattung: Bembidion Latr. Bestimmungstabelle der Bembidion-Arten des palaearktischen Gebietes. (Mit Hinweisen auf holarktische, aethiopische und orientalische Arten). Koleopterologische Rundschau 29: 1/97-70/166." title="Bestimmungs-Tabellen europaeischer Kaefer (9. Stueck). II. Fam. Carabidae, Subfam. Bembidiinae. 66. Gattung: Bembidion Latr. Bestimmungstabelle der Bembidion-Arten des palaearktischen Gebietes. (Mit Hinweisen auf holarktische, aethiopische und orientalische Arten). Koleopterologische Rundschau 29: 1 / 97 - 70 / 166." year="1943 b">Netolitzky (1943b</bibRefCitation>
: 17/113, note 18) mentioned above should be considered. However 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. dimidiatum" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" rank="species" species="dimidiatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">B. dimidiatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
must be included in the subgenus 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bembidion (Euperyphus)" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Euperyphus">Bembidion Euperyphus</taxonomicName>
as currently intended.
</paragraph>
